						>
					</Label>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<Section title='About'>
			<p class='text-muted-foreground'>
				Software Engineer  with a passion for software, mathematics, and quantitative finance. Experienced building pricing and portfolio management systems in the financial services industry. Currently studying a quantitative finance masters at UCL and have a keen interest in the financial markets.
			</p>
		</Section>

		<Section title='Work Experience'>
			<Card
				heading='Software Engineer - Portfolio Management, Ariel Re, London'
				subheading='Full-stack .NET Software Engineer on a small, dynamic and performance-driven development team.'
				date='Mar 2022 - Present'
				imagePath='/src/assets/work.png'
				altText='Full-stack Developer'
				imageClass='h-12 w-auto md:-left-16'
			>
			<ul class='ml-4 list-disc text-muted-foreground'>
				<li>
				Developed front-end Windows desktop applications using WPF and back-end systems in C# and .NET 8.
				</li>
				<li>
				Implemented multithreading to optimize performance, reducing processing time for critical tasks.
				</li>
				<li>
				Built a revenue-generating model for pricing return on capital of insurance-linked securities, weather derivatives, and reinsurance contracts.
				</li>
				<li>
				Integrated third-party APIs, including vendor models, FX rates, and counterparty credit ratings.
				</li>
				<li>
				Designed and implemented a machine learning-based portfolio optimization algorithm to enhance return on capital while ensuring compliance with regulatory constraints.
				</li>
				<li>
				Created a geospatial exposure tool to visualize cedants' exposure from country level to 3-mile grid resolution, supporting hundreds of millions of locations.
				</li>
				<li>
				Mentored junior staff members by collating requirements, peer-reviewing code, and managing stakeholder expectations.
				</li>
			</ul>
			</Card>
			<Card
				heading='Actuarial Data Analyst, IQUW Group, London'
				subheading='Automated financial processes and supported risk decision-making through data visualization.'
				date='Nov 2021 - Mar 2022'
				imagePath='/src/assets/work.png'
				altText='Actuarial Data Analyst'
				imageClass='h-12 w-auto md:-left-16'
			>
			<ul class='ml-4 list-disc text-muted-foreground'>
				<li>
				Automated financial processes using Python, SQL, and VBA, improving efficiency in actuarial workflows.
				</li>
				<li>
				Visualized financial data to support risk decision-making, providing actionable insights to stakeholders.
				</li>
				<li>
				Proposed and implemented automation solutions to streamline actuarial processes.
				</li>
			</ul>
			</Card>
		</Section>

		<Section title='Education'>
			<Card
				heading='University College London, MSc Financial Mathematics'
				subheading='Modules: Machine Learning (Python), Applied Computational Finance (C++), Market Risk and Portfolio Theory, Interest Rates and Credit Modelling and Algorithmic Trading.'
				date='Sep 2024 - June 2026'
				imagePath='/src/assets/education.png'
				altText='UCL'
				imageClass='h-11 w-auto md:-left-16'
			/>
			<Card
				heading='University Of Warwick, BSc (Hons) Mathematics 2:1'
				subheading='Modules: Interdisciplinary Computer Modelling, Maths by Computer, Statistics, Programming for Scientists, Scientific Computing, Computational Physics, and Mathematics of Machine Learning.'
				date='Sep 2018 - July 2021'
				imagePath='/src/assets/education.png'
				altText='Warwick'
				imageClass='h-11 w-auto md:-left-16'
			/>
			<Card
				heading='King Edward VI Aston Sixth Form, A-Levels'
				subheading='A*A*AA in Maths, Further Maths, Physics, and Chemistry. Received the Albert Prize for Mathematics (awarded for achieving the highest A-Level marks in the year group).'
				date='2015 - 2017'
				imagePath='/src/assets/education.png'
				altText='King Edward VI'
				imageClass='h-11 w-auto md:-left-16'
			/>
		</Section>

		<Section title='Skills'>
			<SkillLayout title='Languages' skills={languages} />
			<SkillLayout title='Frontend' skills={frontend} />
			<SkillLayout title='Backend' skills={backend} />
			<SkillLayout title='Others' skills={others} />
		</Section>
	</div>
</PageLayout>
